quran[21]{c,v,t}:
  16,30,"And it will be said to those who fear Allah, “What has your Lord sent down?” They will say, “All that is good.” For those who do good in this world, there is a good reward; and the home of the Hereafter is far better. What an excellent home for those who fear Allah"
  16,31,"They will enter Gardens of Eternity, under which rivers flow. They will have therein whatever they wish. This is how Allah rewards those who fear Allah"
  16,32,"those whose souls the angels take while they are in a state of purity, saying, “Peace be upon you; enter Paradise for what you used to do.”"
  16,33,"Are they [the disbelievers] waiting for the angels to come to them or for the command of your Lord to come? Those who came before them did the same. It was not Allah Who wronged them, but it was they who wronged themselves"
  16,34,"They were afflicted by the evil consequences of their deeds, and they were overwhelmed by what they used to ridicule"
  16,35,"Those who associate partners with Allah say, “If Allah had willed, neither we nor our forefathers would have worshiped anything besides Him, nor would we have prohibited anything without His command.” Those who came before them did the same. Is the duty of the messengers except to convey the message clearly"
  16,36,"Indeed, We sent to every community a messenger, [saying], “Worship Allah and shun false gods.” Among them were some whom Allah guided, while others were destined to stray. So travel through the land and see how was the end of the deniers"
  16,37,"Even though you are keen to guide them, but Allah does not guide those whom He causes to stray, and they will have no helpers"
  16,38,"They swear by Allah their solemn oaths that Allah will not resurrect those who die. Yes He will! It is a true promise upon Him, but most people do not know –"
  16,39,"so that He may make clear to them that over which they differ, and so that the disbelievers may realize that they were liars"
  16,40,"When We intend something, We only say to it, “Be!”, and it is"
  16,41,"Those who migrated for the sake of Allah after being oppressed, We will surely give them good in this world. But the reward of the Hereafter is greater, if only they knew"
  16,42,those who endured patiently and put their trust in their Lord
  16,43,"We did not send before you except men to whom We sent revelation. Ask the people of knowledge, if you do not know"
  16,44,"[We sent them] with clear proofs and scriptures, and We have sent down to you [O Prophet] the Reminder to explain to people what has been sent down to them, and so that they may reflect"
  16,45,Do those who devise evil plots feel secure that Allah will not make them sink into the earth or that the punishment will not come upon them from where they do not expect
  16,46,"Or that He may seize them while they are going about, and they will have no escape"
  16,47,"Or that He will seize them when they are in a state of fear? But your Lord is indeed Ever Gracious, Most Merciful"
  16,48,"Do they not see the things that Allah has created, how their shadows incline to the right and left, prostrating to Allah in all humility"
  16,49,"To Allah prostrates all that is in the heavens and on earth of living things, and so do the angels; and they do not show arrogance"
  16,50,"They fear their Lord above them, and they do what they are commanded"